data.title: Maria de las Mercedes Of Orléans (1860
data.meta_description: Wife of Alfonso XII. Queen of Spain. Died of typhoid fever or tuberculosis two days after her 18th birthday.  She was buried in El Escorial although not in the royal crypt.  On 8 Nov. 2000 her remains were reinterred in Cathedral of la Almudena in Madrid.
